The paper is about improving the performance of NLP tasks using a new architecture that combines the transformer and BLSTM models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments involving GLUE and SQuAD 1.1 datasets, which are commonly used in NLP research, indicating that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
